items.label: 678690a3f1291f24940334fe
items.name: Water Heating Service Rate D5 (Delivery Charge Residential)
items.description:
Available to customers using hot water for sanitary purposes (other uses subject to the approval of the Company) and taking service under Residential and General Service Rate Schedules. Options I and III are also available to customers with solar assisted hot water heaters.
Option I: Available to customers who desire controlled water heating service to all of the heating elements of electric water heaters, the design and method of installation of which are approved by the Company as adapted to this service, taken through a separately metered circuit to which no other load except water heating may be connected.
Option II: Available to customers who desire controlled water heating service to single tank installations of 30 through 120 gallon tank capacity for residential customers, and 40 through 120 gallon tank capacity for commercial customers, the design and method of installation of which are approved by the Company as adapted to this service. This service may be taken combined with normal load through the regular meter with only the lower element controlled. NOT AVAILABLE FOR NEW INSTALLATIONS.
Option III: Available to customers who desire uncontrolled water heating service to installations, the design and method of which are approved by the Company as adapted to this service, taken through a separately metered circuit to which no other load except water heating may be connected.
items.energycomments: Nuclear Surcharge + Base Securitization + Investment Recovery Mechanism + Energy Waste Reduction Surcharge
